@node "history" "This program has a history. So respect it."

Try to understand this:

Some two years ago: @{b}@{u}Matrix Generator 2.0@{ub}@{uu}

Written in AMOS Pro. Here's an excerpt from the Guide:
@{i}
Maybe I'll make a MUI Matrix Generator one day (for I have evolved away from AMOS - ain't I a smart feller?), maybe I'll make a game someday concerning the Matrix, maybe I'll come over to your place and eat your cat. Who knows. It all depends on whether @{b}YOU@{ub} write or not...

Nah, just kidding.
@{ui}
Well, exactly @{b}one@{ub} person wrote in to say he was pleased to find this particular piece of software. (Luckily I didn't make it shareware). And I @{i}did@{ui} make a MUI Matrix Generator. So I @{i}wasn't@{ui} kidding. 

Was I disappointed? No. Because it was mentioned in Amiga Computing, March 1997 issue! Great, or what? AND it had good review too. Just to state my case, and not to blow my trumpet, here goes an(other) excerpt:
@{i}
Shadowrun GMs will therefore consider the Matrix Generator something of a godsend - in a matter of seconds it can generate an entire computer system (...) Whilst it clearly caters for an extremely small number of people, this is the sort of simple but useful program that the Public Domain was made to house.
@{ui}
AC did manage to refer to the wrong file on Aminet and they printed a very ugly screenshot as well. I threatened to chop off both the reviewer's legs if he didn't rectify the erroneous filename, but it didn't work. I didn't even get a reply...

And here's another excerpt from the MatrixGenerator 2.0 Guide:
@{i}
But when I come round to coding a MUI version, it'll be completely bug-free and the constellation thingies will be in there too. And perhaps even more...
@{ui}
So, if @{b}two@{ub} persons write in now and if Amiga Inc. recognises my considerable donation to the Amiga community with a large amount of hard cash (magazine recognition isn't enough anymore!), perhaps I will make a include room for Party IC. Or do you @{i}still@{ui} think I'm kidding? @{i}Eh@{ui}?

